# Design Guidelines

These guidelines ensure that UI implementation across the repository follows consistent UX, accessibility, and design system standards.

These rules are applied during:

- `/plan` when Figma links are provided
- `/implement` when building UI components
- `/review` when validating UI consistency

---

# 1. Design Source of Truth

The **primary source of UI design is Figma**.

If the work-item or feature specification includes **Figma URLs**, the agent must:

1. Analyze the Figma design
2. Identify components used
3. Break UI into reusable components
4. Map design tokens to implementation
5. Include UI implementation steps in the implementation plan

If **multiple Figma URLs exist**, each must be treated as a separate UI context.

Example:

Work item / spec contains:
Figma:
https://figma.com/design/dashboard
https://figma.com/design/user-profile

The plan must include implementation sections for both screens.

If **no Figma link exists**, skip design planning.

---

# 2. Design System Principles

All UI implementations must follow these principles:

### Consistency

Use shared components wherever possible.

Avoid creating duplicate UI components that already exist.

### Reusability

Break UI into reusable components instead of page-specific markup.

Preferred hierarchy:
Page
