# 4. Layout and Spacing Standards

Maintain consistent spacing.

Recommended spacing scale:

4px
8px
12px
16px
24px
32px
48px

Avoid arbitrary spacing like:

margin: 13px
padding: 27px

Spacing must follow the spacing scale.

---

# 5. Typography Standards

Typography must remain consistent across the application.

Hierarchy example:

| Type | Usage |
|-----|------|
| H1 | Page titles |
| H2 | Section titles |
| H3 | Subsections |
| Body | Content |
| Caption | Small labels |

Avoid inline font styling.

Use defined classes or design tokens.

---

# 6. Accessibility Requirements

All UI components must follow accessibility best practices.

### Required standards

- Images must include `alt` attributes
- Buttons must have accessible labels
- Form fields must include labels
- Interactive elements must support keyboard navigation
- Color contrast must meet accessibility guidelines

Example:

Bad:

<button>Submit</button>

Good:

<button aria-label="Submit form">Submit</button>

---

# 7. Responsive Design

All UI must support responsive layouts.

Preferred breakpoints:

Mobile
Tablet
Desktop
Wide screens

Guidelines:

- Avoid fixed widths
- Prefer flexible layouts
- Components should adapt to smaller screens

